title: PPPP’s Pir Syed Salah Shah Jilani wins PS- 83 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP), Pir Syed Salah Shah Jilani has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-83, Dadu -IV, by securing 48,944 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Imdad Hussain Lighari, Grand Democratic Alliance, who bagged 20,712 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 40.72 %.
